<div class="span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module" style="" data-widget-type="custom_widget" data-x="0" data-w="12">
<div id="hs_cos_wrapper_widget_1713585432634" class="hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module" style="" data-hs-cos-general-type="widget" data-hs-cos-type="module">

<div class="two-col-content dnd_padd right_col_no_of_imgsingle  cm_single_media  widget_1713585432634 left key-components-of-voice    ">
  


  






  
  

  <div class="page-center theme_center">


    
    <div>
      


    </div>
    

    <div class="columns_rowo_wrap bottom_row   right_media_image">


      <div class="flex_row  flex_center ">

        
        <div class="content-col col6 ">
          




          <div class="cont-inner">
            <div class="description"><h2 style="line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 16px;">Mobility Solutions for Every Environment</h2>
<p>Heartland delivers smart mobile computing solutions for every environment. So, whether you run a retail storefront, trucking operation, or bustling distribution center, you have access the right solution for every task. We offer a wide range of ergonomic handheld computers, rugged wearables, vehicle-mount tablets and more, to ensure you always have the devices you need for operational success.</p></div>
            

                

                
                  </div>
                </div>
                

                

                
                <div class="media_column img-col col6 ">

                  




                  
                  <div class="mediaimg ">
                           
                    
                    
                    <div class="single-img">
                      
                      
                    </div>
                    
                  </div>
                  




                  

                  
                  <div class="content_box">
                    <div class="text_block">
                      <p style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000;">Rugged devices</span> – Built for harsh environments, rugged mobile computers are engineered to withstand challenging conditions such as extreme temperatures, dust, moisture and drops. Rugged devices are ideal for environments like warehouses, cold storage facilities, manufacturing floors, and field operations.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000;">Handheld computers</span> – Combining the functionality of a scanner, computer, and communication device, handheld computers are versatile and ergonomic, making them ideal for warehouse workers, retail associates or manufacturing technicians. Mobile handhelds allow users to quickly capture and store data without being tied to a fixed workstation.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000;">Wearable computers</span> – PWearable computers provide hands-free scanning and data access. Commonly worn on the wrist or arm, and often paired with headsets, these devices are ideal for high-volume environments where speed, safety, and precision are critical.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 0;"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000;">Vehicle-mount computers</span> – Vehicle-mounted computers (or vehicle mounted units—VMUs) are designed for installation in forklifts, pallet jacks, and delivery trucks. These devices provide real-time data access and communication within arm’s reach while operators remain in motion. VMUs reduce the need for drivers and operators to leave the vehicle, improving productivity and safety.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 0;"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000;">Rugged tablets</span> – Rugged tablets offer maximum mobility with a large screen size, making them perfect for managerial tasks, fieldwork, and customer-facing applications. Many rugged tablets feature modular accessories, including payment readers, keyboard attachments, and docking stations—transforming them into flexible workstations.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  

                  

                </div>
                
                


              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          




          




          







          

        </div>



        


        </div>

